    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-04-17T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-04-17T23:00:00-05:00" n="482"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d482">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/10557: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="5" xml:id="d482fn1">Repeated on the same date to Stockholm
                        as telegram 698.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-04-18T00:00:00-04:00"
                            >April 18, 1944—midnight.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3104. From Crowley<note n="6" xml:id="d482fn2">Leo T. Crowley, Foreign Economic
                        Administrator.</note> and Stone, FEA. We would welcome proposition along
                    lines of your 3117 of April 16 repeated to Stockholm as 134. Any such
                    arrangement with SKF should include assurances that all deliveries of bearing
                    machinery (including tools), special steels as well as ball and roller bearings
                    to enemy Europe will be effectively stopped for the duration of the war.
                    Authorization of funds has been assured by USCC<note n="7" xml:id="d482fn3"
                        >United States Commercial Company.</note> subject to above conditions and
                    satisfactory arrangements with UK authorities for equitable division of costs. A
                    special representative of USCC and FEA, Stanton Griffis, will leave shortly for
                    London and Stockholm with authority to assist in negotiations and consummate
                    deal for USCC.</p>
                <p>Sent to London, repeated to Stockholm. [Crowley and Stone, FEA.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
